## System Name  
**NMPA Clinical Trial & Ethics Management System (CTEMS)**

## Version  
1.0

## Owner  
Clinical Research Oversight Division

## Last Updated  
2026-02-09

---

## 1. Purpose

The NMPA Clinical Trial & Ethics Management System (CTEMS) manages the registration, monitoring, approval, and compliance review of clinical trials conducted for pharmaceutical and medical device products.

The system ensures that all trials comply with ethical standards, regulatory policies, and safety requirements.

---

## 2. Scope

### In Scope
- Clinical trial registration  
- Ethics committee approval  
- Trial document submission  
- Safety reporting  
- Trial monitoring  
- Participant protection  
- Compliance auditing  

### Out of Scope
- Commercial trial funding  
- International trial coordination  

---

## 3. User Roles

| Role              | Description                                |
|-------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| Sponsor           | Registers and manages clinical trials      |
| Reviewer          | Reviews trial protocols and reports        |
| Ethics Officer    | Oversees ethical compliance                |
| Admin             | Manages system configuration               |

---

